On Mon, 8 Apr 2002, Robert S. Whitaker wrote:

> I'm going over my bus engine and discovered that at lease 2 case sealing
> studs have stripped threads.
>
> One of the studs is right behind the crankcase pulley and the other is
> lowest one in back near the bottom of the flywheel.
>
> Can these be fixed with threaded inserts or is a new case in order?

If there is enough metal around the stud, you can use an insert.  The
insert should be stronger than the original thread.

